description:
2008, THE YEAR OF THE OLYMPICS! THE TROLLYMPICS HAVE BEEN DECLARED OPEN, TO ALL COMERS!

Hold on, because it’s going to be a rough ride! You can spot the real trolls by a few little distinguishing features: they’re hairy, they stink, and they’re scared stiff of water... But who will be the best enchanter of all the trolls? The fight between the competitors will be fierce and the Trollympic events are sure to be gruelling! May the best troll win!
name: Trollympiades

description:
THE TROLLS ARE FIERCER THAN EVER – AND JUST AS FUNNY!

Can a good education transform a troll into a socially acceptable creature? That’s the question facing the ladies bountiful, who are obliged to welcome into their orphanage two small trolls with scant regard for rules.
name: Sang famille (I)

description:
THE TROLL TYKES’ ADVENTURES CONTINUE

Can a good education transform a troll into a socially acceptable creature? That’s the question facing the ladies bountiful, who are obliged to welcome into their orphanage two small trolls with scant regard for rules.
name: La guerre des gloutons (II)

description:
THE ALBUM OF THE ORIGINS: THE STORY OF WAHA IN SHORT STORY FORM

The Trolls come back for a volume 0 that tells the origins of the vivacious Waha and completes the great saga of The Trolls of Troy. This new tale, essential to the Troll mythology, mentions one of Eckmül’s best kept secrets…
name: L'histoire de Waha

description:
A NEW ADVENTURE - IN TWO VOLUMES - OF THE MOST FEROCIOUS COMIC-BEST-SELLER EVER!

The trolls are without a doubt the most dangerous creatures of Troy. But what would these terrible predators become if they were magically shrunk to the size of an insect?! Well, even 15cm tall, a troll is still a troll!
name: Boules de poils (I)

description:
A NEW ADVENTURE - IN TWO VOLUMES –OF THE MOST FEROCIOUS COMIC-BEST-SELLER EVER!

The trolls are without a doubt the most dangerous creatures of Troy. But what would these terrible predators become if they were magically shrunk to the size of an insect?! Well, even 15cm tall, a troll is still a troll!
name: Poils de Trolls (II)

description: A flood strikes the village, there`s talk about meta fiction, Manu travels with Mortemont and Capucine gives our heroes a hard time. There`s also a cool Monsieur Henri-strip.
name: Le Déluge

description:
The Punisher and Spider-Man have never seen eye to eye, but this is the Superior Spider-Man! What does Frank Castle think about Spider-Man's new, hard edged attitude?

Plus, Mysterio is BACK! Or is he? The Superior Spider-Man has a few questions for ol' fishbowl head, but the Punisher has something else for him: bullets.
name: Pro-Death

description: Capucine is older now, and Mariette is a student.
name: Les Révolutions

description: Hugo Strange makes a last, desperate attempt to strike Batman where he lives. While The Dark Knight is otherwise engaged behind the walls of Arkham City, Strange’s Tyger Guards descend upon a seemingly undefended Wayne Manor. It’s up to Nightwing, Robin and Alfred to show them they’re not welcome.
name: Uninvited Guests

description:
Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 1: The Big Match
  • Chapter 2: Awkward Patience
  • Chapter 3: A Light, Misleading Argument
  • Chapter 4: An Unrefined Point of View
  • Chapter 5: Grave Understanding
  • Chapter 6: Blue Fragment
  • Chapter 7: A Long Private Message
name: Volume 1

description:
Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 8: Dog Catcher
  • Chapter 9: Dog Catcher 2
  • Chapter 10: Dog's Breakfast
  • Chapter 11: Dog Race
  • Chapter 12: Dog Fight
  • Chapter 13: Dog-Eat-Dog
  • Chapter 14: Dog-Ear
name: Volume 2

description:
Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 15: Take Responsibility!
  • Chapter 16: High School Lullaby
  • Chapter 17: R-R-R-Russian Roulette
  • Chapter 18: Without Preramble, We're On the Street
  • Chapter 19: Roses and Non-Fiction
  • Chapter 20: ?
  • Chapter 21: ?
name: Volume 3

description: Contains The Uncanny X-Men #230 and Marvel Comics Presents #1.
name: "Stille nacht..."

description: Oliver's vendetta continues in the aftermath of "The Undertaking". "Sacrifices" part 2 of 2.
name: Sacrifices, Part 2

description: Contains The Uncanny X-Men #231 and Marvel Comics Presents #2.
name: ... klaar voor het diner

description: The cataclysmic conclusion of the Clone Saga! Peter and Ben grow ever closer to unraveling the twisted conspiracy that has manipulated them both for years, but the identity of the shadowy madman pulling their strings will shock both Spider-Men to the core — and one will not survive! As Mary Jane goes into labor and a vengeful villain makes his return, lies are exposed, truths are revealed and heroes are sacrificed! Plus: Take a peek behind the curtain at what could have been as Marvel’s staffers explore alternate endings to the Clone Saga! And whatever happened to Carrion? Collecting AMAZING SPIDER-MAN (1963) #417-418, SENSATIONAL SPIDER-MAN (1996) #11, SPECTACULAR SPIDER-MAN (1976) #240-241, SPIDER-MAN (1990) #73-75, SPIDER-MAN TEAM-UP #5, SPIDER-MAN UNLIMITED (1993) #14, SPIDER-MAN: REVELATIONS, SPIDER-MAN: THE OSBORN JOURNAL and SPIDER-MAN: 101 WAYS TO END THE CLONE SAGA.
name: Book Six

volume.name: The Amazing Spider-Man: The Complete Ben Reilly Epic

description: Contains The Uncanny X-Men #232 and Marvel Comics Presents #3.
name: Onverwacht gebroed

volume.name: True Tales of the Roller Derby

description: It started with a brutal beating at a pachinko parlor, and now Bakune Young - maniac, moron, or mastermind - has taken Japan's biggest crime boss hostage in step one of his plan to rule the world. Soon, yakuza, police, detectives, and Bakune's ex-gym teacher converge in an apocalypse when Bakune and his captive hole up in Osaka Castle. Even Bakune's fighting skills may not save him this time.
name: Vol. 1

description: Max is bitten, and Remy waits for him to turn into a zombie as Private Beck and his men arrive. Lazlo escapes from his Hollywood vault deathtrap, and Blue Adams makes a choice about his future that changes his life forever. Remy meanwhile meets Harlow in a military quarantine as the issue ends, and Amanda Hocking's best selling novel HOLLOWLAND begins, adapted and enhanced by #1 New York Times bestseller Tony Lee (X-Men Unlimited, Doctor Who), with outstanding artwork by Steve Uy (Avengers Initiative, JSA Classified)! Dynamite Entertainment proudly presents Amanda Hocking's The Hollows: A Hollowland graphic novel.
name: Movin' On

volume.name: Amanda Hocking's The Hollows: A Hollowland Graphic Novel

description: Hangovers don't come much worse than this... Tommy 'Irish' Flynn awakes from his bar-room battering to face a military court chaired by his mysterious assailants. The enigmatic MI6 Agent Huntington-Moss wants Irish to guide them to the Pacific Island site that saw Flynn's Squad annihilated in a Dinosaur attack. But the island is home to other monsters too: The SS are there to claim the creatures for themselves. Convincing Irish to return to the site of his worst nightmares proves to be just the beginning...
name: Chapter Two: In Like Flynn

description:
THE HOTTEST NEW ALL-AGES COMIC ON THE STANDS! Join Rigby the Raccoon and Mordeci the Bluejay on a regular day that's anything but! Written by acclaimed cartoonist KC Green (GUNSHOW) and featuring the hottest indie talent in comics on the covers! DON'T MISS OUT ON THIS NEW ALL-AGES SENSATION!

Note: The digital edition (6/12/2013) for this issue was released early.

Humanity is a tricky thing. This is the topic of discussion as 034 and Orlee share a heart-to-heart two weeks following the events that brought the solider back to Subterra. Meanwhile, Cole finds his failures have led him out of the good graces of his father and into the awaiting arms of something far more sinister.

The second issue of Adam Cadwell's acclaimed slacker-vampire series introduces Mike, Douglas and Arianna, three vampires who spend most of their time arguing about the blood buying rota until Mike witnesses a strange death on New Year's Eve which leads them all into even weirder territory.
name: 20th Century Vamp, Part 2

description: Our hero has been searching Albuquerque for a couple of months now without any luck. But tonight, his luck changes. The question is... was it for better, or worse?
When the truth behind Thomasina's magical troubles are revealed, a strange world full of whimsy opens up before her! Has her dream come true, or are her problems truly beginning?

Annie and Kat have settled their dispute and settled into their new quarters for the year. Kat pursues her robot theory, and along with Annie and some of the other robots for support, she starts to build an innovative robot the likes of which has never been seen before.
name: Faraway Morning

description: The Garda investigate the murders at the Holy Numbers centre and discover a link to a previous murder. Raymond Nolan gets very bad news but continues on his hunt for the truth.

This is the one you've been waiting for! Riley vs. the Regent! Captured by the Regent and sentenced to exile, Riley must accept her destiny - as the savior of humankind. The only thing standing in her way is Regent Steig. It's a fight to the death that will change the course of Hoodlum forever!
Joe struggles to bring Kinski home but can he get back in time to save his job?

From the Shuster award winning creators of Least I Could Do and Gutters comes a loving nod to classic fantasy novels that manages to flip the genre on it's head. Unlikely heros cut a swath through a fantasy world that is extremely familiar and yet very different. A naive elven hunter makes an strange friend in an undead warlock and the two manage to make both enemies and friends as they fight the good fight against the Legaran Empire.
An old school Mask has returned to Golden City and isn't too happy to learn about the death of his old partner... Doctor Daylight. Are Bobby Silver and the Mobsters days numbered?

McCaw closes in on the truth as Glitter's attempts to escape Moth City lead her into dangerous company, the city's communist underbelly is revealed, and the Nationalists take extreme measures to keep the bizarre effects of the weapon contained.
name: Season 2 (Part 1 of 2)

description: The companions are scattered. One of them lies charred and dead and another runs headlong into the furnace that burned his brethren. As peril constricts around them all, escape has become their only hope and they look north for safety and cover.

person_credits.name: Terry LaBan
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

volume.name: Love's Not a Three Dollar Fare

person_credits.name: Scott Roberts
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

person_credits.name: Charles M. Schulz
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: The 10th Muse meets Victoria's Secret Service for the 1st time. Greek mythology has documented the nine Muses, the inspirational daughters of the almighty Zeus. But history forgot one-- the 10th Muse. Introducing this very special collected edition, written by 10th Muse creator Darren G. Davis and featuring art by Batgirl's Vincente Cifuentes.
name: Volume 7

description: In futuristic L.A. where neo-tribes inhabit the urban sprawl, a reluctant leader named Marne is warned that a "Black Network" inside the LAPD is hunting down tribal leaders and she's next on the list! When Marne discovers a secret dimension that can be accessed by a drug called Accelerate, she decides take on her enemies to save her tribe. Written by novelist Richard Kadrey (Sandman Slim series, Butcher Bird), Illustrated by the Pander Brothers (Grendel, Secret Broadcast, Triple-X International).

Count on Nate Wright to stir things up and make his entrance with a splash! Aspiring cartoonist Nate Wright is the star of Big Nate, the daily and Sunday comic strip. As a popular middle-grade book character, Nate is 11 years old, four-and-a-half feet tall, and the all-time record holder for detentions in school history. He's a self-described genius and sixth grade Renaissance Man. Nate, who lives with his dad and older sister, enjoys pestering his family and teachers with his sarcasm.
name: GN

description: Leave it to Big Nate to stake his claim on anything in reach! Aspiring cartoonist Nate Wright is the star of Big Nate, the daily and Sunday comic strip. As a popular middle-grade book character, Nate is 11 years old, four-and-a-half feet tall, and the all-time record holder for detentions in school history. He's a self-described genius and sixth grade Renaissance Man. Nate, who lives with his dad and older sister, enjoys pestering his family and teachers with his sarcasm.
name: GN

volume.name: Big Nate: Dibs On This Chair

description: Nate Wright has a nose (and a penchant) for trouble. So he's not one to be surprised by a pop quiz popping up. Aspiring cartoonist Nate Wright is the star of Big Nate, the daily and Sunday comic strip and a favorite middle-grade book character. Nate is 11 years old, four-and-a-half feet tall, and the all-time record holder for detentions in school history. He's a self-described genius and sixth grade Renaissance Man. Nate, who lives with his dad and older sister, enjoys pestering his family and teachers with his sarcasm.
name: GN

volume.name: Big Nate: I Smell A Pop Quiz!

description: Big Nate, who is always notoriously unprepared for class, turns to divine intervention to spare him! Aspiring cartoonist Nate Wright is the star of Big Nate, the daily and Sunday comic strip. As a popular middle-grade book character, Nate is 11 years old, four-and-a-half feet tall, and the all-time record holder for detentions in school history. He's a self-described genius and sixth grade Renaissance Man. Nate, who lives with his dad and older sister, enjoys pestering his family and teachers with his sarcasm.
name: GN

volume.name: Big Nate: Pray For A Fire Drill

description: Binary the graphic novel is based on Christopher Hinz's novel, Liege-Killer, which won the Compton Crook Award in 1988, and has garnered a cult following. Liege-Killer is part of a trilogy, which includes Ash Ock and The Paratwa. In Liege-Killer, human experimentation on human embryos in the near future produced a new species: the Paratwa, a single consciousness occupying telepathically linked bodies. The Paratwa are highly skilled warriors but look like normal people and are not necessarily identical twins, and can even be a pair of male and female. The books follow the activities of humans and Paratwa as these old enemies are reunited more than a century after the earth's apocalypse during which humans had thought the Paratwa race had become extinct.
name: GN

description: Simon has been trained with the skill of crossing into alternate realities at will. After Simon has a vision of the multiverse being destroyed, he seeks out the help of his friend Ethan, a man with the ability to turn into a magical rabbit named Kole. Together they hope to find the source of the vision before it's too late.

"Do a story on Cole Adams, the music producer." Lauren, a music reporter, couldn't believe her ears when the boss gave her the assignment. "It may be my job, but I have to do a story on the ex-boyfriend with whom I ended so badly?" Lauren diligently waits at the Grammy Awards for Cole to show up. When he does, Cole sweeps her away in his car! "I'm glad to see you again, Lauren." Why does he smile at her as if nothing has changed? Is this reunion "the start of something new"? n>
name: Vol. 1

description: Sakae Sugiura working hard to become a teacher, gets an assistant teacher position at an elementary school. There he meets his old elementary school homeroom teacher, Ryuji Fukada. Fukada-Sensei was someone Sakae looked up to, someone who supported him. Now, Sakae is shocked by how different Fukada is and feels lost. But since he's no longer a student, will his feelings towards Fukada change...?
name: Vol. 1

volume.name: The Color of the Clear Blue Sky

description:
Straight from the pages of the hit digital series DOUBLE BARREL! You've never seen a Cold War like this! In Crater XV, the follow-up to 2009's Eisner-nominated Far Arden, Kevin Cannon weaves together an intoxicating tale of swashbuckling adventure, abandoned moon bases, bloodthirsty walruses, rogue astronauts, two-faced femme fatales, sailboat chases, Siberian pirates, international Arctic politics, and a gaggle of horny orphans. Mixed up in all of this are Army Shanks, our salty sea dog still reeling from a devastating loss, and Wendy Byrd, a plucky teenager who wants nothing more than a one-way ticket off the face of the Earth. For mystery, thrills, and Arctic chills, set a course for Crater XV!

Note: The digital edition (6/12/2013) was released two weeks before the print edition (6/26/2013).
name: GN

description: When Donald accidentally punctures his cousin Fethry's new inflatable pool, he incurs a huge bill for the damaage. With this hanging over his head, he tries to help Fethry sell his cool new product. Unfortunately for Donald, Fethry's sales pitch is, well, full of hot air.

volume.name: Donald Duck and the Backyard Beach

description: Bored with the idea of another summer at home, Donald Duck enters a "chain vacation" contest, with the hopes of winning the "Best Vacationer's" prize: another free vacation! Donald is confident that he'll win, but the title "Best Vacationer" isn't bestowed on just anybody...

volume.name: Donald Duck and the Vacation Chain

description: Scrooge McDuck wants to make a very profitable bargain with a golf-loving millionaire. But the deal will only be sealed if one of Scrooge's relatives can become a golf champion! So here comes Donald Duck...with his unbeatable bad luck!

Introducing the newest promising young talent, Victoria Justice! As a singer, song-writer, dancer, AND actress, Justice is the ultimate Renaissance woman. She got her start on the popular Nickelodeon television show iCarly before earning her very own show called Victorious. Next up for Justice is the release of her debut, full-length album, due out in 2013. Discover the story behind her impressive talent in FAME: Victoria Justice.

1 & 2 Kings and 1 & 2 Chronicles tell the history of Israel and Judah following the Davidic dynasty through the exile in Babylon. Against this historical backdrop of the rise and fall of maneuvering kings and warring empires, the fictional series Kingdoms traces in vivid manga style the saga of the dedicated advisor Iddo and his descendants. As he remains loyal to the memory of the just King Josiah and labors to keep his nation faithful to the Lord, Iddo struggles to protect his own family. Destruction looms from the East… while danger lurks within. When the Lord calls him as the prophet to the nations, Jeremiah doesn’t know that faithfulness to God often results in mistreatment from others. As he proclaims the word of the Lord to Judah, false prophets and royal officials try to silence him. But as Babylon’s army surrounds Jerusalem, the king and people of Judah must choose either to heed God’s instructions, or suffer destruction.
name: The Prophet's Oracle

description: Discover the collected life stories of J.K. Rowling, Stephenie Meyer, Charlaine Harris, and Anne Rice in this broad examination of strong women that have made a difference in today's literature. These Female Force biographical comics have been featured on The View, in People, the Chicago Tribune, USA Today, and thousands of other media outlets.
name: TPB

description: Foreign intervention comes at a price, but with rioting in the streets, natural resources running low and the economic horizon bleak, America is forced to accept international entries to the Death Race. The president's only hope of regaining national pride is by Frankenstein Junior becoming king of the road!

Country life is too hectic for poor Gus Goose! What he needs is a nice, relaxing vacation! But on vacation the desperately longed-for rest seems out of reach... especially when a strange energy takes possession of Gus Goose, transforming him into the best entertainer of the season!

volume.name: Gus Goose and the Unexpectedly Lively Vacation

description: Straight from the pages of the hit digital series DOUBLE BARREL! It's his own personal Hell. After the funeral of his estranged father, faded hometown hero Hector "Heck" Hammarskjöld finds himself the new owner of the old man's house... and inside it, a portal to the underworld! With few other prospects on the horizon, Heck goes into business settling inheritance disputes by contacting the recently deceased, accompanied by his faithful sidekick Elliot. But when an old flame knocks on their door with an important message for her late husband, Heck and Elliot embark on an terrifying journey down into the nine circles, braving the horrors of Hell for an assignment that will reveal more than they ever imagined. Award-winning cartoonist Zander Cannon (The Replacement God, Top 10, Smax, The Stuff of Life) collects his serial from the hit digital magazine Double Barrel into his long-awaited first graphic novel: a story of memory, friendship, and regret, where the past is dead and buried... but not out of reach.
name: GN

description: Izumi is a dedicated single parent haunted by his past while trying hard to make a future for him and his son. First suffering the crippling loss of his closest friend after their junior high graduation in what was an ego destroying personal rejection of their friendship, he then went on to lose his young wife due to complications of childbirth. Thankfully, his seemingly tough yakuza brother in law, Sawaragi, was there to lend a hand when he needed it most. Things seem to be going swimmingly well until his childhood friend makes a sudden reappearance, throwing Izumi into emotional turmoil. Just what is Takatsudo playing at, wanting to hang out like close friends again after all this time? Izumi's determined to find out just what is going on before his heart is crushed beyond repair this time...
name: Vol. 1

description: Grab the Last Call "All Aboard Bundle" for a limited time only! The Ghost Train is the unearthly engine that travels between dimensions and through the void of space and time. When two normal teenagers, Alec and Sam, mysteriously end up on the train, they're thrown into a world unlike any they've ever seen and in the middle of a killing spree more chilling than anything they could have imagined! After being separated in Volume 1, the pair finally find one another, but it's not the a to catch up though! There's still the issue of who is murdering the passengers and how it's connected to the boy's appearance on the train!
name: TPB

volume.name: The Last Call: The All Aboard Bundle

description: Jacque and Liza were once deeply in love. They shared many happy moments until she discovered she was pregnant. Jacque had never wanted to have a child and always told her, "What I can give you is passion and friendship, no more than that." Therefore, she decided to raise the child alone and left Jacque without telling him anything. Three years have passed since then, when Liza unexpectedly meets him again. Knowing nothing about what happened to her 3 years ago, Jacque tries to seduce her, full of passion and irresistible charm. How can Liza keep hiding their child from him?
name: Vol. 1

description:
After the acclaimed indie film Save the Date and the bestselling all-ages humor book Darth Vader and Son, graphic novelist Jeffrey Brown (Clumsy, Unlikely) returns to the autobiographical work that first made his reputation. In A Matter of Life, Jeffrey Brown draws upon memories of three generations of Brown men: himself, his minister father, and his preschooler son Oscar. Weaving through time, passing through the quiet suburbs and colorful cities of the midwest, their stories slowly assemble into a kaleidoscopic answer to the big questions: matters of life and death, family and faith, and the search for something beyond oneself.

Note: The digital edition (6/12/2013) was released almost a month before the print edition (July 3, 2013).
name: GN

description: Fishing and fun are what Mickey and Goofy have in mind...but it's not what they're going to get! Strange disappearances have upset the relaxing vacation the friends have planned...

volume.name: Mickey Mouse and the Portable Tele-Transporter

description: Minoo Shirazi is a rebellious young Iranian woman, struggling to define herself amidst the strict social conventions of an oppressive regime, and the differing wishes of an overbearing father, in between life in Iran and life in midwestern America. Minoo Shirazi is also a free-spirited adventurer in a fantasy world, a place where aspects of modern America and ancient Persia meld into a unique landscape. And yet, neither of these women are the true Minoo Shirazi. At the intersection of guilt and freedom, family and self, ancient myths and modern enigmas, lies...Persia Blues.
name: Volume 1

description: From acclaimed Doctor Who novelist David McIntee comes a new Ray Harryhausen Presents adventure! The quest to find the Golden Fleece is over, but now Jason and his band of Argonauts must embark on a new and more difficult journey -- the journey home! Pursued by a vengeful Aeetes, the Argonauts will brave many dangers, encounter old friends and new, and face enemies also both old and new. But when the gods play games, no one can avoid reaching the lands of the dead forever!
name: TPB

volume.name: Ray Harryhausen Presents: Jason & the Argonauts - Kingdom of Hades

description: When the spread of the deadly Sanctus plague decimates the established government, people turn to the Church, and Pope Augustus for sanctuary. Unbeknownst to the populace, Pope Augustus is a sadistic and power obsessed bastion of evil. As the Dark Pope's ambitions amplify, only an ex-cop, an eight year old girl, and her foul-mouthed possessed rag doll, stand alone against the onslaught of the Dark Pope, and his army of Shadowmen.
name: Volume 1

volume.name: Sanctus: Kings or Pawns of Men

description: Oscar is an 80 year old, retired detective who longs to return to his former career. When he disappears, Deputy Woods investigates Oscar's past and discovers he is not the man he appears to be.
name: The Case of the Toothless Fairy

description: Written by Mark Poulton (Savage Hawkman, Avengelyne) with art by Jim Hanna and Marat Mychaels (Deadpool Corps, Grifter), Spotlight is Entourage meets the Justice League. As Spotlight, Tyler James is Hollywood's brightest star. He Navigates the challenges of celebrity and being a superhero with a close knit group of friends until a girl enters the inner circle, putting a strain on the relationship between him and his best friend, Mikey. Now, that jealousy has reared its ugly head, Spotlight soon learns the cost of fame and finds out who his real friends truly are.
name: GN

description:
Straight from the pages of our FCBD Preview, The Steam Engines of Oz has arrived! Find out how the Emerald City has transformed in the last 100 years as Victoria Wright and her friends plot their escape only to fall into the clutches of a terrifying threat. This re-imagining of Oz through a SteamPunk lens is a must read for fans of Oz, steampunk, an exciting story, and fantastic art!

Note: The digital edition (6/12/2013) for this issue was released almost a month before the print edition (7/3/2013).
